com.googlecode.cqengine.persistence.support

Class ObjectSet<O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.persistence.support.ObjectSet<O>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloseableIterable<O>, Closeable, AutoCloseable, Iterable<O>

    public abstract class ObjectSet<O>
extends Object
implements CloseableIterable<O>, Closeable
    Represents a set of objects which may be iterated repeatedly, allowing the resources opened for each iteration to be closed afterwards.

    The CloseableIterable.iterator() method returns a CloseableIterator which should ideally be closed after each iteration is complete.

    However this object also keeps track of iterators which were opened but not yet closed, and provides a close() method which will close all iterators which remain open.

    Author:
    npgall
